NAME Jupiter.translators_comments: Al-Mushtari is the native proper name for Jupiter, derived from shining like lightning. See Ref. # 2.

NAME Mars.translators_comments: Al-Merrikh is the native proper name for Mars, derived from Marakh (ARABIC: مرخ), a plant which is used to start fire. See Ref. # 2.

NAME Mercury.translators_comments: Utarid is the native proper name for Mercury, derived from unstableness (mercurial).  See Ref. # 2.

NAME Moon.translators_comments: Al-Qamar is the native proper name for the Moon, derived from strong whiteness.  See Ref. # 2. and Taj al-Arous lexicon.

NAME Saturn.translators_comments: Zuhal is the native proper name for Saturn, derived from remoteness.  See Ref. # 2.

NAME Sun.translators_comments: Ush-shams is the native proper name for the Sun.

NAME Venus.translators_comments: Az- Zuharah is the native proper name for Venus, derived from brightness and beauty. See Ref. # 2.
